'''Acomb''' is a village in [[Northumberland]], in [[England]]. It is situated to the north of [[Hexham]]<ref>[http://www.durham.gov.uk/durhamcc/K2P.nsf/K2PDetail?readform&PRN=N12976 Local History]</ref>, not far from the junction of the [[A69 road]] and [[A6079 road]]. The name is Anglo-Saxon Old English ''acum'', 'at the oak trees'.

